docs.abstract: On his first campaign stop for the Martin Luther King holiday in South Carolina, Joe Biden denounced the president in some of his strongest language yet.
docs.snippet: On his first campaign stop for the Martin Luther King holiday in South Carolina, Joe Biden denounced the president in some of his strongest language yet.
docs.lead_paragraph: COLUMBIA, S.C. — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. paid a visit to Sunday services at Bethlehem Baptist Church, a large black congregation here, urging the crowd to fight back against hatred and condemning President Trump in some of his strongest language yet for heightening racial divisions in the country.

headline.main: Mentioning Trump and K.K.K. in Same Sentence, Biden Condemns Hate
headline.print_headline: Naming Trump and Klan In the Same Sentence, Biden Condemns Hate

docs.abstract: While demanding that an opponent, Pete Buttigieg, disclose his McKinsey clients, Ms. Warren provided a fuller explanation of her compensation as a legal consultant.
docs.snippet: While demanding that an opponent, Pete Buttigieg, disclose his McKinsey clients, Ms. Warren provided a fuller explanation of her compensation as a legal consultant.
docs.lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren disclosed a detailed list of compensation she received during 30 years of moonlighting as a legal consultant — about $1.9 million in all — as she and Mayor Pete Buttigieg continued a back-and-forth demanding transparency in the race for the Democratic presidential nomination.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren Earned $1.9 Million Over 3 Decades for Corporate and Legal Work
headline.print_headline: Warren Discloses $1.9 Million in Earnings as Consultant

docs.abstract: Campaigns and super PACs aren’t supposed to work together, but social media is blurring the lines.
docs.snippet: Campaigns and super PACs aren’t supposed to work together, but social media is blurring the lines.
docs.lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Nick Corasaniti, your host on Tuesdays for our coverage of all things media and messaging, writing to you from Las Vegas, where the leading Democratic presidential candidates are set to debate tomorrow night.

headline.main: Watchdog Says Buttigieg Campaign Exploited Super PAC Loophole
headline.print_headline: Social Media, a Super PAC Loophole

docs.abstract: After he had a heart attack in October, Bernie Sanders said he would release ‘comprehensive’ medical records. But he has not done so.
docs.snippet: After he had a heart attack in October, Bernie Sanders said he would release ‘comprehensive’ medical records. But he has not done so.
docs.lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — Ahead of a crucial Democratic debate on Wednesday night, Bernie Sanders is facing new pressure to release his full medical records, more than four months after he had a heart attack while campaigning and vowed he would provide “comprehensive” records on his health.

headline.main: Sanders Suggests He Won’t Release Full Medical Records
headline.print_headline: Sanders Suggests He Won’t Share Full Medical Records

docs.abstract: After watching the disaster in Iowa, Nevada party officials are scrambling to find other ways to count and report results later this month.
docs.snippet: After watching the disaster in Iowa, Nevada party officials are scrambling to find other ways to count and report results later this month.
docs.lead_paragraph: After abandoning plans to use the same kind of app that led to a debacle in Iowa, Nevada Democratic officials are testing backup plans this weekend as they attempt to come up with a clear alternative for their own state caucus, which begins in less than two weeks.

headline.main: Nevada Democrats Test a Caucus Plan ‘Without Something You Can Download on Your Phone’

docs.abstract: State party officials released new details about their plans on Thursday, but after the chaos in Iowa, campaigns are worried that their months of effort in Nevada could go to waste.
docs.snippet: State party officials released new details about their plans on Thursday, but after the chaos in Iowa, campaigns are worried that their months of effort in Nevada could go to waste.
docs.lead_paragraph: In the hours after the Iowa caucuses last Monday, officials with the Nevada Democrats watched cable news with increasing alarm. They were supposed to use a similar app to count the results of their own caucuses weeks later. Their questions to Iowa officials and the technology developers went unanswered.

headline.main: The Nevada Caucuses Are Up Next. Will They Unfold Smoothly?
headline.print_headline: In Nevada, the Caucuses Loom, and Nervousness Rises Among Democrats

docs.abstract: Bernie Sanders’s campaign said it would request the more intensive step of a recount after the state party announced that it had changed results in 29 precincts but that no national delegates would be moved.
docs.snippet: Bernie Sanders’s campaign said it would request the more intensive step of a recount after the state party announced that it had changed results in 29 precincts but that no national delegates would be moved.
docs.lead_paragraph: The Iowa Democratic Party announced on Tuesday that it had completed its partial recanvass, changing results in 29 precincts but shifting no national delegates.

headline.main: Iowa Democrats Complete Recanvass, but No Delegates Are Shifted
headline.print_headline: No Iowa Delegates Are Shifted After Recanvass by Democrats
